body:
Looks like an NVIDIA driver issue.

- Make sure you have NVIDIA GPU and drivers, or
- Try waifu2x-ncnn-vulkan.
I'm using a 2070 super with the latest driver atm. I will try the waifu2x-ncnn-vulkan later on.
I tried waifu2x-ncnn-vulkan and it worked, but I forgot how to change the resolution. How do you pick which resolution you want?

waifu2x-ncnn-vulkan doesn't support output resolution, only scaling ratio.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21986859/89317173-8be3de00-d66c-11ea-8824-49572d527d96.png)
Anyway to get waifu2x to work than? I want to upscale out at an output resolution.
Your error looks like a driver issue. Try verifying that your GPU driver is the latest.
I use Geforce experience to update my driver and it says I have the latest already.
Why did you close the issue? Did you manage to solve it?
No, I closed it on accident. I did not solve it yet. I reinstalled my driver today and will check later if I still get the problem.
yea, after reinstalling my gpu driver, waifu2x caffe works correctly now.

rip nvm, I got the error again, I forgot to change the height and width last time. Maybe it's something to do with that or me changing the output to .mkv.
[video2x_2020-08-09_23-26-18.log](https://github.com/k4yt3x/video2x/files/5052462/video2x_2020-08-09_23-26-18.log)
Changing the output to MKV shouldn't break it. Does it start upscaling correctly if you specify only the scaling ratio?
Yea, I did that the first time and it worked. Second time, I realized that I forgot to change it and tried it than the error popped up.

Doesn't make sense, that simple difference shouldn't be causing any problems.
How many processes are you using?
Sorry new to this, what do you mean by processes? I only have 1 GPU and 1 CPU and only run the video2x gui with no other programs up

Oh I just mean if you've changed this value at all.
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21986859/89950806-ddb2d800-dc19-11ea-8210-cd4e5e19eedf.png)
Nope, left that on by default. Oh, it might be the scale ratio. I put it at 3.0 and changed the Waifu2x resolution setting to 1920x1080. I'll test it out later.

Yea, I tried again and still got an error. Guess I can't use Waifu2x than. :l Maybe its my Waifu2x settings? Is there anything wrong with it? [https://i.gyazo.com/d8f41065e1b1f9e092aa53d47e12d3ce.png](url)
[video2x_2020-08-15_22-36-14.log](https://github.com/k4yt3x/video2x/files/5081114/video2x_2020-08-15_22-36-14.log)
You've set it to cuDNN mode. Do you have cuDNN installed properly?
Oh, maybe that's the issue. I thought I already have cuDNN when I updated my driver, is cuDNN a good option or should I use the other ones? I can install it if cuDNN make's it look better.

cuDNN doesn't help with quality, only speed. Actually thinking about it I don't remember exactly how much speed improvement you'd be looking at, but I do remember it's pretty significant.

On a side note here, waifu2x-ncnn-vulkan is way faster, while delivering comparable quality. If you're okay with manually adjusting the resolution after upscaling, it would be a better choice.
Hm, how do I manual adjust the resolution after upscaling?
You'll ether have to use FFmpeg directly or use some editing software like Premiere Pro.
Do you know any guides to do it on ffmpeg?
